args:
Guided by the mysterious woman who shares
Zethia's face, the prince arrives at the Binding
Ruins, where his sister and Emperor Aurelius
await. The party follows them deeper into
the ruins.
The woman with my sister's face came to us\nagain and claimed that Zethia and the\nemperor were waiting in the Binding Ruins.
And so we made for the location where\nFather once sought a new Shard.
What is the emperor's aim in all this?\nAnd are the ruins also home to the\nlast of the Six Greatwyrms?
What awaits us in this ancient place so deeply\ntied to the Alberian line of kings?
On the road to the Binding Ruins...
Bloody 'ell! The cursed Empire put our\nfields and 'omes to the torch, and now\nthere ain't nothin' left but ash!
Nowheres to go, and no food for our\nbellies? We'll soon be ashes too, we will!
This road leads to the Mistholt,\nwhere an old castle awaits.
If you have nowhere else to go, you can\nmake that place your refuge. The Empire\nwill not be able to harm you there.
Now make haste for the Mistholt.\nAnd may the goddess guide your travels!
Just some good neighbors doin'\ngood neighborly things.
Society is starting to come apart at the\nseams. I fear the human bill for the\nEmpire's coup will soon come due.
We have to make this right, and soon.\nIt's not just about Zethia anymore—all of\nAlberia's people are waiting for a rescue.
Hurry, then! The Binding Ruins lie ahead.
You don't need to tell me twice.
This place is one of many sealing sites\nscattered across the continent.
Inside each is a great slumbering evil.
And to keep that evil sealed away,\nthere is a Sacred Shard.
Be ever watchful in this place.
The mana here is warped—it's far too\ndark and stagnant to be natural.
What could possibly have happened\nhere to make the air so foul?
Oh, how I loathe this place.
It's the same feeling that king gives off.\nIt sets my scales on edge.
The man who resembles King Aurelius,\nyou mean?
Was it not after he came here that\nhe underwent his transformation,\nYour Highness?
Then perhaps something happened to\nKing Aurelius here, and we are bearing\nwitness to the result...
Yes, provided my memory holds true,\nshe should... Aaah!
Whoa, the look-alike went all...flickery!\nYou all right, lady?!
Go! Waste no time on me.\nI will follow as soon as—
Gone again. Ain't nothin' about that\nwoman what makes a damn bit of sense.
No, but she was right about not wasting\ntime. If Zethia's here, we need to hurry.
*cough* Cleo wasn't kiddin' about this\njoint. Just bein' here feels lousy!
We barely walked inside and I'm already\ngettin' woozy. Plus my legs feel like\nthey're made'a stone.
I fare no better. Something is clearly\namiss in this place.
How do you find yourself, Your Highness?
Well enough to keep moving.\nBut thanks for the concern.
And you're correct that this place is wrong.\nBut I don't understand why the royal family\ntook such pains to keep it secret.
I would assume it holds something of\ngrave importance to the bloodline.\nOr to the entire kingdom.
Everybody shut your yaps!\nI hear someone up ahead!
...Still have grave reservations about\nleaving the two of them without an escort.\nWhat if something were to happen?
We were bade wait for His Highness and\nLady Zethia to return, so here we wait.
Along with whatever is pretending to be\nmy father.
We oughta be able to circle 'round these\nchumps without bein' noticed. C'mon!
